Next, observe that the kernel of 
\begin_inset Formula $\varphi$
\end_inset

 is given by 
\begin_inset Formula $I_{1}\cdots I_{k}$
\end_inset

.
 Indeed, 
\begin_inset Formula $\varphi(r)=0$
\end_inset

 if and only if 
\begin_inset Formula $r+I_{j}=I_{j}$
\end_inset

 for all 
\begin_inset Formula $j=1,\dots,k$
\end_inset

 if and only if 
\begin_inset Formula $r\in I_{1}\cap\cdots\cap I_{k}=I_{1}\cdots I_{k}$
\end_inset

.
 The theorem now follows from the first isomorphism theorem for rings.
 
